content:
The Avatar component provides a way to display user profile pictures or initials.

## Exports

- **Avatar**: The root component for the avatar. Accepts standard `<img>` props or children for fallback content.
- **AvatarImage**: The component for displaying the avatar image. Should be a child of `Avatar`.
- **AvatarFallback**: The component for displaying fallback content (e.g., initials) when the image cannot be loaded. Should be a child of `Avatar`.

## Usage

```tsx
import { Avatar, AvatarImage, AvatarFallback } from '@/components/ui/avatar';

function UserProfile() {
  return (
    <Avatar>
      <AvatarImage src="https://github.com/shadcn.png" alt="@shadcn" />
      <AvatarFallback>CN</AvatarFallback>
    </Avatar>
  );
}

export default UserProfile;
```
